<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-318-322  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 318 322.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  May 29 1989 v6 n21 p70(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Poor domestic sales force DEC to freeze salaries of U.S. workers.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Burke, Steven.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Equipment Corp. (salaries, etc.).andO;Ticker:    DEC.andO;Topic:     SalaryProfitFinancial Stability.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Poor Domestic Sales Force DEC To Freeze Salaries of U.S.andP;  WorkersandM;Blaming poor domestic sales, Digital Equipment Corp. is freezing the salariesof its 73,500 U.S.andP;  employees beginning July 2.andM;&quot;Business is down in the U.S.andP;  for Digital, as it is for the industry ingeneral, and we have to control costs in order to restore profitability inthe U.S.,&quot; said Digital spokeswoman Nikki Richardson.andM;The freeze delays annual salary reviews of U.S.andP;  employees for at least threemonths.andP;  The company will decide at the end of September whether to continuethe salary policy.andP;  Digital's 52,000 employees outside the United States arenot affected.andM;Rumors of pending layoffs among U.S.andP;  employees have swept through Digital inrecent weeks, but Richardson denied them.andP;  &quot;No layoff or early-retirementincentive program is planned,&quot; she said.andM;Digital has reduced its U.S.andP;  work force by 200 employees through attritionin the last quarter.andP;  Its international work force has increased by 1,200employees during the same period.andM;Company executives say they are examining a variety of programs to controlU.S.andP;  costs.andP;  Analysts say the Maynard, Mass., company has cut back itscapital-spending budget for this year by about $300 million.andM;Barry Willman, an analyst with Sanford C. Bernstein andamp; Co., a New Yorkinvestment house, said he expects Digital's earnings for the rest of 1989 tocome in lower than those for last year.andP;  He also expects a rebound in 1990,when the company introduces a top-of-the-line minicomputer.andO;</TEXT></DOC>